<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4751321>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 19. Stellapora echinata. (a) Branch cross section revealing gastrostyles, dactylopore spines and ampullae cavities. (b) Gastrostyles. (c) Surface of colony displaying flush gastropores, slightly raised dactylopores, dactylopore spines and ampullae. (d) Longitudinal slit on dactylopore spine. (e) Laterally-fused dactylopore spines forming transluscent lamella. (f) Coenosteal pores and perforated slits. (g) Stellate gastropores, coenosteal pores and flush/slightly raised dactylopores." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4751321/files/figure.png" .

